notify /ˈnəʊtɪˌfaɪ/

(notifying,notified,notifies) 

1. V-T If you notify someone of something, you officially inform them about it. 通知 [正式] 

例： The skipper notified the coastguard of the tragedy. 船长通知了海岸警卫队这一灾难。 

例： Earlier this year they were notified that their homes were to be cleared away. 今年早些时候他们被通知说他们的家将被拆除。

